    {
      "id": "m6qlbtfp",
      "questionNumber": 5,
      "questionText": "<p>Total number of sigma (σ) _______ and pi(π) ______ bonds respectively present in hex-1-en-4-yne are:</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>14 and 3</p>",
        "<p>11 and 3</p>",
        "<p>13 and 3</p>",
        "<p>3 and 13</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "properties-and-preparation-of-alkynes",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>The compound given is hex - 1 - en - 4 - yne</p>\n<p>Structure is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7o9mydh/ba471a80-eb82-403c-ad8e-4b9f498c1f3e/6b5a8b50-f58b-11ef-b727-73cb4ca4a481/file-jaoe38c1m7o9mydi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7o9mydh/ba471a80-eb82-403c-ad8e-4b9f498c1f3e/6b5a8b50-f58b-11ef-b727-73cb4ca4a481/file-jaoe38c1m7o9mydi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 38 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>a double bond has one $\\pi$ bond and one sigma bond.</p>\n<p>A triple bond has one $\\sigma$ bond and two $\\pi$ bonds.</p>\n<p>So, the number of $\\pi$ bonds $=1+2=3$</p>\n<p>For sigma bonds, count all carbon $-$ carbon bonds and carbon $-$ hydrogen bonds except the $\\pi$ bonds in double bond and triple bond.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7o9oys7/a726336a-5edf-412f-9afa-4ad41e67fcf6/a349b270-f58b-11ef-b727-73cb4ca4a481/file-jaoe38c1m7o9oys8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7o9oys7/a726336a-5edf-412f-9afa-4ad41e67fcf6/a349b270-f58b-11ef-b727-73cb4ca4a481/file-jaoe38c1m7o9oys8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 38 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>The number of sigma bonds = 13</p>\n<p>So, total number of bonds $\\Rightarrow \\sigma=13\\quad \\pi=3$</p>\n<p>Answer : option (C) 13 and 3</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
